One-Week DevOps Job Preparation Schedule
Daily Overview
6:00 AM - 8:00 AM: Study DevOps Topics
8:00 AM - 9:00 AM: Freshen up and Breakfast
9:00 AM - 10:00 AM: Commute to Work
10:00 AM - 1:00 PM: Hands-on Practice and Learning (Use free time effectively)
1:00 PM - 2:00 PM: Lunch Break
2:00 PM - 4:00 PM: Continue Hands-on Practice and Learning
4:00 PM - 6:00 PM: Commute Home
6:00 PM - 7:00 PM: Dinner and Relax
7:00 PM - 9:00 PM: English Communication Practice and Mock Interviews

Weekly Topic Breakdown
Day 1: DevOps Fundamentals & AWS Overview
6:00 AM - 8:00 AM: Study DevOps principles, Agile methodology, and CI/CD concepts.
10:00 AM - 1:00 PM: Explore AWS core services (EC2, S3, IAM); focus on hands-on AWS tasks.
2:00 PM - 4:00 PM: Continue AWS hands-on practice (create EC2 instances, configure S3).
7:00 PM - 9:00 PM: Practice speaking about DevOps concepts; summarize your notes.

Day 2: CI/CD with Jenkins
6:00 AM - 8:00 AM: Refresh Jenkins installation, configuration, and pipeline creation.
10:00 AM - 1:00 PM: Create a CI/CD pipeline project integrating GitHub with Jenkins.
2:00 PM - 4:00 PM: Hands-on practice with Jenkins (build and deploy applications).
7:00 PM - 9:00 PM: Conduct mock interviews focusing on CI/CD practices and scenarios.

Day 3: Containerization with Docker
6:00 AM - 8:00 AM: Review Docker basics, including images, containers, and Docker Hub.
10:00 AM - 1:00 PM: Build and run Docker containers; practice creating Dockerfiles.
2:00 PM - 4:00 PM: Learn about Docker Compose and multi-container applications.
7:00 PM - 9:00 PM: Summarize Docker best practices; discuss your learnings.

Day 4: Infrastructure as Code with Terraform
6:00 AM - 8:00 AM: Refresh Terraform fundamentals, including state files and modules.
10:00 AM - 1:00 PM: Write Terraform scripts to create and manage AWS infrastructure.
2:00 PM - 4:00 PM: Practice Terraform commands and workflows (apply, plan, destroy).
7:00 PM - 9:00 PM: Discuss your Terraform scripts and infrastructure designs.

Day 5: Orchestration with Kubernetes
6:00 AM - 8:00 AM: Review Kubernetes architecture, Pods, and Services.
10:00 AM - 1:00 PM: Set up a local Kubernetes cluster (Minikube/Docker Desktop) and deploy an application.
2:00 PM - 4:00 PM: Explore Kubernetes commands (kubectl) and configuration.
7:00 PM - 9:00 PM: Mock interviews focusing on Kubernetes concepts and scenarios.

Day 6: Configuration Management with Ansible
6:00 AM - 8:00 AM: Review Ansible architecture and how to write playbooks.
10:00 AM - 1:00 PM: Write and execute Ansible playbooks for configuration management tasks.
2:00 PM - 4:00 PM: Learn about Ansible roles and inventory management.
7:00 PM - 9:00 PM: Summarize your Ansible learning and engage in discussions.

Day 7: Review and Mock Interviews
6:00 AM - 8:00 AM: Revise all topics covered during the week.
10:00 AM - 1:00 PM: Hands-on practice or mini-project integrating multiple tools (CI/CD pipeline with Docker and Kubernetes).
2:00 PM - 4:00 PM: Review and consolidate notes; finalize your learning outcomes.
7:00 PM - 9:00 PM: Conduct comprehensive mock interviews covering all topics.


Tips for Staying Engaged While Studying
Active Learning: Engage with the material actively by summarizing, teaching others, or applying concepts in hands-on projects.
Stay Hydrated and Snack Wisely: Keep water and healthy snacks on hand to maintain energy.
Short Breaks: Take 5-10 minute breaks between study sessions to recharge.
